cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NA 

This paper deals with super-resolution techniques for 3-D images using tensor factorization and deep learning methods. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper focuses on image enhancement and segmentation. The use of tensor factorization also suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning), as this is a common technique in that field. The paper also mentions an offline estimate of the system point spread function, which could relate to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the comparison with a state-of-the-art iterative technique suggests a possible fit with cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
